caption: Absolutely awesome value to quantity (and quality) for a "boba joint"!  We've gone back a half-dozen times for ramen/udon and their tasty appetizers.  Each time, quality has been equal or better than other sit down places that charge double.  Hands down a great way to feed the family!
My kids' favorite Bobba tea, and mine too, of all the ones we tried! The chocolate one and matcha tea- perfect!
I ordered the fish and chip. Fish is very good, but the chip is the worst. Barely cook! Cut corners!
Food took around 30mins to come out, but it was yummy 😋
Has My favorite taro milk tea with lychee jelly
Kiddos enjoy boba drinks..... But I asked for non-caffeinated drink and was told all tea have caffeine 🧐
Super long lives, good tea
Love this place! But be aware that it always has a long line and I've waited up to a hour to order.

The lines are way to long. Front register girl was taking phone calls with 40 people in line out the door. Triage ability isn't working. So I left and didn't get my Jasmine tea.

Drinks are good. I'm new to drinking Boba so I'm unsure what to get. So far I tried the strawberry lemonade green tea with Lychee in it. They have a few vegetarian options. I like their fried tofu and fries
From what I heard we can always rely on all the food T4 has its always clean
Solid quality boba. One of my go-to places in the area.
The drinks were amazing and the downside was that they took too long for the order to be done and I waited for I would say 1hour for my food and drinks

I'm giving them for stars primarily because they have good sanitation and they seal up everything nice for take outs.
This t4 the best t4 ever made. Cyril the owner is such a cool and nice guy. This t4 just hit different
Love this place.  Milk tea... munchies and open late. Affordable. Reward system for frequent usage .Wifi. Electric outlets for you laptop or gaming phones. Large tables for groups.

Love this T4 the Best! They have the best service and the best boba. Always excellent service. The manager takes a lot of pride in his store and is very customer service friendly. I enjoy kist grabbing a tea and hanging out. Great atmosphere to study in also.
They make the best Thai tea 😍
Tasty boba and fun ambient anime songs.
Offers a vast range of boba/milk teas, smoothies, milkshakes, juices, fried snacks, ramen, and rice dishes. Great place to socialize.
I got a nosebleed while eating the spicy beef udon and fled in a panic but food was good.
So many varieties, most excellent. Just remember not to go when school has just gotten out, or you could wait quite a while to get you served.
its an okay place for a quick snack or tea. which the staff was more friendly
reliably good and customers are fun to watch and talk to, too.

This is my favorite boba shop. If you're hungry, order the popcorn chicken with minced pork rice, and add in some corn. Really good!!
I wouldn't know what their products are like because they wouldn't break $50 on a $20 order that I stood in line for 15 minutes on a Friday night. So I'll give them 2 stars for the atmosphere.

I visited for the first time today, stopping in for popcorn chicken.  I had thought to get a quick snack on my way home.  Sadly, they seem to have forgotten about my order, so I waited half an hour for my food.  The basil chicken was fine, the same as you'll get in any similar shop.  But I'll think twice before choosing them again.
Great place to hang out, good variety of drinks, snacks, and food. You can ask for games like cards and Jenga.
Slow service

Bubble tea, popcorn chicken, and egg puffs. If you have a craving this place fills that need. It's a little messy and it's not the best bubble tea place in Chinatown but it does the trick. T4 is open late and a popular nighttime haunt for highschool students in Oakland Chinatown.
Cute decor, fast service, friendly employees! I think any place I can get boba and fried chicken from for $10 or under is a win.
Great selection of milkteas. Ballet chocolate is a must-try
Great product staff didn't seem very happy to there
Good value food and great drinks. Prices have crept up, but California costs always increase sadly.
Great

Great ramen!! I ordered the pork ramen with garlic oil broth and it was delicious. You have some good options like ramen or other kind of Asian tapas like takoyaki and tons of options for drink like different types of smoothies and lots of Asian teas. The service is fast and helpful.
QQ rice bowl is the best! Ground pork and Curry chicken for only $9. Can't beat it with a stick!

Fell into this place while sweating profusely and in need of hydration. Weird tapioca balls in bottom of iced tea....this is a thing?  Kinda cool/fun, tasty mushy treats with every draw on the straw. I liked it. Lots of cool teens darting in and out. Good vibe.
Very good
The first place I went to as soon as I got here and definitely better than anything I have at home. Got the Pearl milk tea and an order of takoyaki. Definitely would recommend

Love the teas! Love the staff! A bit small, but it's Oakland, businesses are small.

Brings me back to Taiwan! The fried calamari really hits the homey spot that I was missing a lot. The saltiness and spiciness of your snacks could be customized by your own with the salt/pepper shakers after you get the food which is great. Boba was underrated. Great pearls super Q
Great!

Good bubble tea in downtown Oakland
Extremely fast service, kind workers and clean (restrooms too)

T4 is my go-to boba shop in Oakland rn mostly because it's closest to where I live and quality is consistent.  The chicken is pretty good, def recommend if you are looking for a snack. Haven't tried the other food options but I see a lot of people come in for the ramen.

I love this place. Lots of options, the staff is super sweet, and it's a great place to hang with friends. It does get pretty crowded at times though. So don't hold your breath on getting a table around lunch time. Oh and always ask about the new additions. There's always a special or some new crazy twist happening.

Located in Oakland Chinatown. We visited after a Friday dinner with our 2 kids to get boba drinks.  Pretty popular as most T4s are, and the line moved well. Consistent quality and good service.

Great boba spot. This is like the authentic stuff if you're into it. Also hella late night snacks to stock up on.
Nice boba place, the drinks are good enough.

Your standard milk tea joint. They have tasty snacks and customizable drinks. I usually come here at night and it can get crowded. The tables aren't always clean but that doesn't make me worry about my food.

It's decent. Happy Hour 8pm+: Stuff are a percent off and some drinks.  The service is helpful. There are a lot of tables to eat your food. The food I tried are the Basil Popcorn Chicken and Garlic Chicken wings; which are really good. Some of the drinks taste like water.

Great place to hang out and eat and drink teas. They have a wide selection of teas to try with the option for adding to lessing ice and sweetness. Prices are reasonable and affordable and they have food choices as well. Try out their basil and popcorn chicken and egg puffs with matcha.
